  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Autonomic dysreflexia in high spinal cord-injured can be initiated by a full bladder or
      bowel, or when trying to empty either. This randomised study aims at evaluating whether
      irrigation procedure or digital stimulation or evacuation of the rectum is less provocative
      of autonomic dysreflexia. Participants have their bowels emptied on different days, in the
      morning fasting. Bladder filling with sterile saline water is evaluated on a third day as a
      control.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
